commitResults.messageTitle: feat: Handle duplicate persons from data
commitResults.messageBody:
The JsonSerializableAddressBook class has been modified
to handle duplicate persons in the address book.
The code now logs a warning message
when a duplicate person is encountered and
continues processing the remaining persons.
The exisitng contact will be kept.
This ensures that the address book does not contain duplicate entries.

Updated JsonSerializableAddressBookTest
to assert successful handling of duplicate persons

The JsonSerializableAddressBookTest class has been updated
to assert the successful handling of duplicate persons.
The test now verifies that when a JSON file
with duplicate persons is read,
the resulting AddressBook object contains only unique persons.

commitResults.messageTitle: chore: Add test for duplicate person
feat: Handle person data with illegal value
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit update the way person data with illegal value is handled.
Originally, one or more illegal value will result in
the whole data file being treated as corrupted.
The app will then start on a clean slate.

Now, if a person data contain(s) illegal value(s),
only that particular person data will be discarded.
Person data with no issue will be kept and read as usual.
However, if any other part of the file is corrupted,
it will still discard the whole file
and start on a clean slate as per previous version.

This update improves the usability of the application
and minimises data loss.
